SHR Reference Model Version 1.0.0
shr.finding

Element Evaluation

Documentation:
Parent class for question/answer or measurement/value findings regarding the value of a property or aspect of a subject. Includes lab tests, measurements, observations, social, behavioral findings.
Ancestors:

      DataAbsentReason
      Provides a reason why the value of the observation is missing, if it is expected (some observations are not expected to have a value).
      		 shr.finding.DataAbsentReason
      None
      		 0..1 N/A
      QuestionCode
      What the finding concerns, for example, height, blood pressure, disease status, wound dimensions, diabetes risk, condition present, condition absent, etc. The observed entity is sometimes posed as a question, a property, or a test code.
      		 shr.finding.QuestionCode
      None
      		 1..1 N/A
      Components
      Components are parts of the parent observation. Component observations share the same attributes (such as Specimen) as the primary observation and are not separable. However, the reference range may be different for each component observation.
      		 shr.finding.Components
      None
      		 0..1 N/A
